txt.en: A cut!
'Hoy! What have we here?'
A strike!
'Well, this will whet their appetites!'
A blow!
'Get up! Get up! There's foes sneaking right beneath our noses!'
<gutteral hum>
The Ruined City
'Noooooo!'
'And leave the hilt. And take the tip of truth to warn my masters.'
'Break and warn.'
'Break.'
'Die.'
This place... <sniffs> has been a grave for many. And the dead... the dead are my friends.
You will join the dead. And become my playthings.
You are frail... living... you cannot withstand.
Say Faramir lived. Say he returned to the White City. What a tale of unconquerable odds he would tell!
Hope is a thing that shall die. And with it, the frail candles of your lives!
'Stick them full of arrows! Cut them with your swords!'
'You. You have dragged behind me wherever I've gone.'
'Thrug's loose! To arms! Get the rope! We need more rope!'
'Like this cloak, this mantle given to me by Faramir. Before he fled. Before... when I was LÃºmithil.'
'Look, there. The enemy in our midst!'
'Grrrrrrrr.'
'March, you maggots. Or you'll all be whipped for impudence!'
'Keep marching or I'll--what's that, now? Sneaking, lurking foes is what!'
'Before I served the Eye. Before I wielded... power.'
'Hey, what's that there? Get 'em!'
'Rah! Grr. Grrrrrrm!'
'You fool. He would have talked.'
'You. Let me look into your eyes. You know... dangerous things. I will break you. Like the Morgul blade that broke in me.'
'Are you lucky fools or fearsome foes, to have come this far?'
'Raaaaaaaaaaaaaah!'
'Call me a fool again and I'll make you howl.'
'A gift is what you are, for you shall win me favour with the Eye.'
'Bloody... little.... Orcs!'
'Men of Harad! To arms!'
'Now you listen. We're not to drink a drop more till word comes down. And no talk-back!'
